storyInfo: Skadi witnesses the local inhabitants' unusual ceremony for seeking food from the ocean. An indignant young Inquisitor breaks it up, and maintains firmly that Skadi is a wicked Ægir, engaging her in a fight.

attributes.content: Ah, you're back! I was just about to go find you.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: How come you've got sand stuck to you... did you go to the shore?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I told you not to go! But you just don't listen.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Hurry, come inside with me, it's warm.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: No need.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Fine. This is for you! I found something to eat. I gave those clothes I half-sewed to Uncle Fireplace, and took some things from his. He's got quite a lot of food left, so he shouldn't mind it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It'll be forever before winter comes. If I just work at it a little more, I'm sure I'll find materials to use.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: This shellmeat...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Just what is it you're eating?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ow! It hurts when you grab me like that... you're much too strong!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What is it you're eating...?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: We—We pick them off the coast!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: There is no food in the sea here. Nothing to harvest whatsoever. This part of the ocean is silent.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I told you, if you went to the shore today, of course there'd be nothing to eat.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: The time has to come...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What time?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: One-hundred...
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: One-hundred!
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: Oh, no! I hadn't even paid attention to the count. We're already at a hundred, then.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.text: As if receiving some sort of signal, each 'busied' person scattered all across the street assembles together.
From all their mouths the same number comes, as they surround a pot, one after another remove something identical thing from it, and then silently leave.

attributes.content: That pot.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Weren't you asking me where all the food came from?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: On every hundredth flood and ebb of the tide, the grownups all get together like this, and each one takes a shell out from it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: The shells in the pot are mostly white ones, and only one is red.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Once the sun's gone down, the one who's taken the red one will go to the shore.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: And on morning the next day, there'll be food all over the shore.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: And the one who went?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Went to go live in the sea. Just as the laws say.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You believe in this too?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Well, where else do you think they go?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: One-hundred. It has finally come.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Here, Woodframe, why that face? This is a good day!
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Very soon, out of us, another lucky one will be chosen. They will leave before us, to live a better life.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Come tomorrow, we will even have, fresh food aplenty. We will all survive. No matter whether gone to the sea, or left on the shore.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: You do not need to worry. You are already old enough. Very soon you will join this too, and have this greatest, opportunity.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: For now, you may go on as before. Give your blessings to that sibling.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sheetmetal, I, I...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You have fallen over. Truly hopeless. What happened at the shore, earlier, weakened your leg.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I do not understand why. I, I am so hungry... I have no strength. I am ill... I am going to die.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: That is right, what about the shell? The one I just drew...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You dropped it on the ground.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Is it... Is it a red one?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Can, I go to live in the sea?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: In the sea, I will not hunger. Is that not right, Sheetmetal? I will live, a good life.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You will... erk, bless me too, as the priest told, will you not?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You have mistaken it.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Take it, for this is your shell. Look carefully at, what color it is. Do not let the saltwater muddle your eyes.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: A white one? Why would it be white... did I see wrong? I could not have. My eyes, are very fine.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: (Plucks strings)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You are here too.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: So this, is how you use that thing.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: *cough*, Sheetmetal, the shell in your hand... your hand, is clutched so tight. It is bleeding, is it not? I can see, reddest red...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: If it's blessings you want, I have none for you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You understand nothing.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: This is what is truly meaningful. I know, at least, where I should go. I will very soon learn.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: What are you all doing?!
That outfit... it's an Inquisitor!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What is an Inquisitor doing here all of a sudden? They come so rarely.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It was so many years ago when an Inquisitor last came... I was still very young then, and we were all living miserably.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: We couldn't find any more food in the city, and so many of us were ill. Everything was a mess, and everyday people passed away.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: The Inquisitors took a few people away. Those people never came back.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Since then, the days have gotten a little better. We still starve, or die of illness, but at least we won't, um, we won't...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I mean... that's an Inquisitor.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Shh, singer, don't anger her. She doesn't seem very happy at all.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I've seen what's happening here, and I've even heard it. You're plotting to send someone into the sea... Do you not know what it is you're trying to do?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Speak! Why won't you speak? I don't like it, I don't like anything about this place. Disease, famine... I thought I'd have seen it here, with how hard it is to escape from.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: According to prior reports, none of you should even be alive at this point, after all these years!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yet reality begs to differ. You all seem to me in better shape than I'd imagined, yet blighted all too fiercely.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Do you all understand what your actions will eventually cause?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Look at me, answer me! Don't you know who I am?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You are an Inquisitor.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: Thus, you are required to answer me, citizen!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: This is the ocean's choice. The one who is chosen is the one who accepts it.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: This isn't right! What in the world is the ocean's choice? As if the ocean had some kind of will of its own... a truly unsound suggestion!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The way I see it, you are conducting a collective murder! How could anyone entering the sea survive? On... on what basis do you sentence the innocent?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Entering the sea, is not death.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: How do you know?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Do you know?
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: I... That's irrelevant. I only know that their departure will in all likelihood be more terrible than death itself.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: And right now, I witness that you are coercing one amongst you.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: We are not making them do it. This is their own choice.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: If they want to go to the shore, we should not obstruct them. The laws do not say they cannot do this.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: Unbridled nonsense! This is not in any way proper!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Then, what is proper? You are an Inquisitor. You may indicate to us.
attributes.name: Inhabitant

attributes.content: At the very least, I know more about wrong than you all seem to.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: What you're carrying out is impermissible conduct. Whether you see it or not, I still smell an odor of wickedness—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: (Draws sword)
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It seems you have no fear of my sword. Perhaps, though, you truly don't consider this a homicide.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You fear not even death. You're all becoming monsters before my very eyes.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Or yet... I suppose there's someone who wants you turned into monsters.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It may be your insanity was tugged astray by some actor. I will unearth this sin's source, I swear!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I'm out of here.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She's the one who can't hold it in. It's nothing to do with me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Who... Who's she? Do you mean... the Inquisitor?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Let's at least let her try.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You've looked in an awful lot of houses this whole way.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You don't need to follow me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Can you really find who you're looking for, turning through one building after another like this?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'll keep looking, then.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Traveling the city north to south, west to east, would take a whole day or two.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: If you didn't follow me, I could move faster.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Does the one who wanted you here know you're looking for her? Didn't she mention any specific place?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Ugh, it'll be dark in just a bit, so let's rest up. Singer, have you readied anywhere to stay tonight?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Anywhere will do.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You can head back with me. I've mentioned the buildings in the north are a little better for wear. Plenty of us all live together.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Look, there was still a little fin oil left over from last time. Uncle Fireplace was up early to light the lamps, and now the room's nice and bright.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'll be fine.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.text: Skadi randomly kicks open a roadside door. The door belongs to a half-collapsed building.

attributes.content: I'll stay in here.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: This one? This one hasn't had anyone in it for forever.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I don't care about that.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Never mind a bed, you'd barely find a single even nook in there. If you can't lie down, how are you going to sleep?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Standing, sitting. It makes no difference.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Incredible...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You're so strange. I didn't know what wandering singers were like, but the feeling you give me isn't like them.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I thought people who love singing would all love laughing, joking. Not like you, you barely talk.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: And would people who love dancing not mind sitting somewhere dust-caked like you are, getting your skirt all dirty?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You should go home.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Are you annoyed with me now?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: This is no good place. As you said.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: But I want to keep you company.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I don't need company.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ugh, I realized. You've stared outside the whole time you've been here. Where are you looking at? The shore, the chapel?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Are you going to head out again at night? Say, climb the hill, and take a look inside the chapel?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: That is none of your business.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: True, it isn't. I'm just curious.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Take it.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Your harp? What are you giving me this for?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You've been eyeing it the whole time. If you want it, just take it.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What a pretty harp.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: (Plink-plunk)
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Such a nice sound. But I have no clue what to do with it. I can only watch you use it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Then what do you want?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Do you feel as though I'm only following you because I want what's yours?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I just want to follow you, really.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I know the only thing on your mind is finding someone, finding that fellow one of yours.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I need to verify a few things.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You've been searching for her for many years now, haven't you?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That's the feeling you give me. The moment I mention finding her, the look in your eyes is different. They're the eyes of someone who's been on so very many journeys. There's times when the look in Grandma Petra's eyes is the same.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: So wonderful. I think, in the end, you can free yourself from her.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Burdens like this are too heavy.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I don't understand what you mean.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: No matter how long you persist for, come twenty or thirty years' time, whether it's you or her, you'll only want to be freed.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: And no one can persist for that long of a time, besides.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What are you saying here?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I'm saying, you might just be the kind who's fated exceptionally well. You don't have to search for her anymore.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Here, only those without any burden can live for very long. If their minds are fixated on one thing for so long, they go mad.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Don't take me just for someone young. I've seen a lot of people go mad.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You don't understand.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I don't understand what happened between you in the past. But things of the past, good or bad, can crush people once too much amasses.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Just like I'm unsure if Grandma Petra's illness has gotten worse, every time she brings up the name Manuel.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You're still young. You don't need to live such a hard life.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Things aren't as simple as that.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Simple or not, you can try talking about it all the same.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'll be right here. I want to hear.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: They're...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Even if I don't pay them mind, they won't just leave.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: The more I don't pay them mind, the more they'll come find you, drown you...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Here, you drink some too.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: (She tilts her head and gulps.)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Stop—not too much in one go, leave a drop for me. I need some too to help with sleepless nights.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Goddamn. You piece of work, you.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: My ass, you're the disaster. You got Juan killed... This damnable papá couldn't even give you an earful in time before you came back looking half-dead. What the hell can I even say to you?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: I can't. A tomar por culo. I can't deal with it.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: ...I'm sorry.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: The enemy's aim was me. No one who nears me... has a happy end.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Look at what you're saying. Cursing me, aren't you?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: You should keep your distance from me too.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That I can do. Don't have to ask me twice.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: All right, sichtír, that doesn't mean I believe you're some ill omen. This line of work's bloodthirsty, and that little idiot didn't listen to his papá, died, and died in some goddamn mystery asshole's hands. If even you couldn't do anything, did I ever have a chance?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: That's not a hatred I can avenge. I've got nothing I can do to you either.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Once we're done with this bit of drink, we'll be off again, going wherever we go.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You bastard! Were you always like this? Can't even find a single kind word, not so much as a profanity, huh?!
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: I've never been too good at the language here. I'm still not.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Nah. You're just not willing to admit you've made a friend.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Dammit. If we're to part, you might as well spare a couple more words. Where are you heading next?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: I don't know.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Same as ever, then. Drifting here and there, taking on missions with no point, fighting wave after wave of enemies who couldn't even take you if you were using one finger. Like living in an unending dream, isn't that?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Skadi tilts back and swigs. But the alcohol seems without a shred of effect on her.
Then where can I go, in your opinion?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You're all bounty hunters in order to make money, to live.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: But I long since had nothing left.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It's savage, orderless. There's not even an automatic toilet. I don't want to be here, and this place doesn't need me. Why should I be here?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Weak, ignorant. Both plainly insatiable yet scared of dying. The things don't even understand me, yet when they come looking for me, they're not even willing to get out of the way.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I can't figure it out.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hold it, did you just crush a few bottles?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Beheading prey. Disposing of enemies. I'm born to do this.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: They all die, and I live on. What do I live on for? Why do these disasters always come calling, but never kill me... always the ones by my side?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Juan was a good person.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I don't need you to tell me, you damned Ægir hag!
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Then why? Why is it always them who die?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I await, I search, I make sure all those shadows pursuing me will be slain, but I can't even find them, I can't even catch sight of them.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: So what am I meant to do? What can I even do, except keep far away from everyone?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Who can even... tell me at this point?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Fine, fine. You win. Tah-hathek.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: This whole bottle's yours. Down it, give crying your eyes out a go, like me. Then get some proper sleep.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: It doesn't do much. I've already tried.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Go dream actual dreams, hunter. For you, dreams might just be the more real thing. You never know, maybe you'll find some clues in there—you know, like a, uh, treasure map that only belongs to you?
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: Find it. And then you can be on your way all the better. Cover your head and move forward. It beats being stuck circling in place.
attributes.name: Old José

attributes.content: A treasure map.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Singer? Are you okay?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You seemed very pained for a moment... I didn't know you could make that sort of face.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It's fine.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And then you started pinching this thing. If you didn't treasure it so, I would've believed it was some awful artifact that angered you so much you wanted to pulverize it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You don't... look angry at all.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: This is hers.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Her? The fellow person you're looking for? Fine, I can see you just won't give up.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: ...She's not a burden.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She's the... one who helped me. She revealed the course of a craft to me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: If I keep following its direction and sailing on, maybe I'll be able to find answers.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Singer, what are you looking for?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I still don't know. It may be who I am. It may be what I should do.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: When... When you're searching for things in the ruins, do you know what you're possibly going to find?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Wow. Put like that, I actually don't know.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I think, once I've found it I'll know.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Let me in!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Shoot.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer, don't you cross words with her. Open the door.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You're not an Iberian.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Say what you will.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That's an Inquisitor. Hmm...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I know you're in there! Don't get cocky about your disguise, I saw you the moment you entered the city!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Open the door, citizen. You don't know what kind of person you're sheltering...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Sheltering? No, I, I didn't mean to hide her...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'll give you a count of three. If you don't open up, don't blame me for being discourteous.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: One, two—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Three! *cough*, *cough* *cough*, so much dust! How long has this place been uninhabited...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Aha, Ægir, I've found you!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: The Inquisitor's blade is keen and swift, the air itself practically sundered in two.
The one meant for the blade's downswing turns her waist, sliding to the side in one unfathomable motion.
She keeps close with the blade's point, and it follows her unerringly, yet it cannot split even one of her hairs.

attributes.content: Wh—What fast moves—
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer... did you dodge?! That posture... I can't imagine it myself.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Stood on the chair... the backrest? People can stand on that? How is she stood so steadily?!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: A fluke and no more!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I must see for sure, how long can your good luck last you?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: She dodged again! In a single swish—she went from this end of the house to that... She's even lighter than seagrass flung in a gale, even faster!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: That stick of yours is useless against me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: St... Stick?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: This is an affront...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You will pay for your false words!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Whoaaa—so strong too! The chair split apart, the cupboard, and now there's even a crack through the floor!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I—I can't bear to watch... oh, the singer...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Wait, she's alright? She evaded all of that? Such nimbleness!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: No... it doesn't seem like she's dodging. Her steps aren't forced in any way. It actually has a peculiar feel of rhythm to it...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: So—So beautiful.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.text: Sweat drips from the young Inquisitor's flushed face. Her blade hand is still steady, but her breaths are coming faster.
The narrow room is cut to utter pieces. To Skadi, this is no different to her slow ambles across the open barrens.

attributes.content: How long do you plan to hide, Ægir?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Like the rest of your kind, you steal into our country, stowing away in the shadows—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Heyah!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Did that slant away? The slash cut against the wall...?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Has the Inquisitor... tired out?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Heh! At no moment does my sword ever slant—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The—The wall collapsed!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: How fortunate, we're on the other side...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: But the singer... has no way out now. The Inquisitor did that intentionally.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Nowhere left to hide.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Take this blow, for it is your crimes put on trial!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Damn it.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Gh... how?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: How can my blade be so casually blocked?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Though I have not used all my strength... person of Ægir, just what are you?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: A wandering singer.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Drivel! I've been following you ever since you entered Sal Viento.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Who are you fooling? What wandering singer... has such skills?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Seems Mister José wasted his effort.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And who is this José?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: And your acts at the shore! I saw it all!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: The Inquisitor flurries her blade, hacking and slashing, thrusting, each blow coming quicker, more exact than the last.

She no longer simply charges the Ægir in her gaze, but relentlessly switches angles, blitzing slices through the surrounding space. If the enemy shows no openings, her swordhand will force the openings from them.
However, Skadi is open, head to toe. She has no intent of defending at all.
Every supple strike melts, one by one, into a traceless muffle.

attributes.content: Confess! Why have you stolen into our land?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You care too much.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: S—So strong!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She's not just unafraid of the Inquisitor, she's taunting her?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It might not be a taunt. The singer just speaks this way. I've gotten used to it after half the day. But... *cough*, now the Inquisitor is even angrier.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I am an... Inquisitor!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: All things that occur in Iberia are my business.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: All errors proscribed under the law... we find, we even out.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: There's something not right about the sea here. Their numbers have grown. This city is on the eve of... no, perhaps it has already become a lair of evils.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Speak, Ægir. All these abnormalities, they are all your doing, correct?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It was you who brought about disaster, had those things assemble here—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You inculcated heretical thought into the citizens here, drove them to enter the sea. Look at them, they've all now become as grotesque as you!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You undoubtedly saw it. You clearly brought something about in the ocean here. Yet see the look in your eyes—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You simply—do not care!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Mm...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: How can such indifference claim resemblance to a normal human? And you dare to say this wasn't your doing?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I will not let you escape, Ægiii—iiir! Do you consider the calamity you've brought to this country a trifle? Your lot are scheming something, of this I am absolutely certain!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What's the Inquisitor talking about?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: The singer's only been here for half a day... and what disaster? Who's grotesque?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Don't we... voluntarily enter the sea?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What other Ægir are there?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I don't understand.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You can't overcome me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: How can we know without trying further?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: This is a pure waste of time.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Tch. You're correct. What have I been wasting all this talk on you for?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I should have long since—apprehended you first.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: All of a sudden, the Inquisitor sheathes her blade. From her side she draws a handcannon, grips it in both hands, and aims at Skadi.

attributes.content: Huh?!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Get down. Don't come out.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Heh, do you know my might now, Ægir?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: (She brushes off her hem.)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: An extra bullet hole. Can't return this to Mister José in original condition now.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You... You! You're without a scratch?! How could you be? My aim was true!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Are you finished?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Your weapon. You don't use it lightly.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Otherwise, you wouldn't be talking to me now. You ought to aim a second time.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I don't understand what you're talking about, nor do I care.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I don't want to...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.text: A beam of light pierces the dead of night, shone directly on Skadi's face.
At the far end of the road, from where the light came, appears a single figure carrying a lamp.
Skadi's face shows no expression, her impatience just now gone with it.
But in the instant she sees that not-so-bright light, the Inquisitor's face shines.
